@namespace TheCanalaveLibrary.SharedUI

@* Self-contained composite mounted inside StoryCard's caret dropdown (Feature 51,
   WU-CustomLists) — same discipline as StoryViewStats: owns its own service injection (in the
   Inner half) so the card stays injection-free, and keeps the menu open while interacting.
   Deliberately in the caret menu, NOT beside the interaction buttons (settled 2026-07-13 — not
   prime real estate). Authenticated-only via AuthorizeView; anonymous viewers see nothing.
   Lists load on first expand (on-demand, like the view-stats reveal). Toggle rows add/remove the
   story; the inline "New list" input creates a private list and adds the story in one step.

   Injection-free wrapper (MA-403, 2026-07-18): the real content + @inject live in
   AddToCustomListMenuInner, instantiated only when AuthorizeView renders Authorized — deferring DI
   resolution until we actually know the viewer is authenticated. See layer3-logic.md "Deferring DI
   Behind AuthorizeView (WU43)" — @inject on THIS component would resolve at construction time
   regardless of the AuthorizeView decision, forcing every StoryCard/StoryDeck consumer's tests to
   register ICustomListWriteService even when testing an anonymous viewer. *@

<AuthorizeView>
    <Authorized>
        <AddToCustomListMenuInner StoryId="@StoryId" />
    </Authorized>
</AuthorizeView>

@code {
    [Parameter, EditorRequired] public int StoryId { get; set; }
}
